caption: Great foods n service..n affordable wooobhooo
Strong coffee and yummy pastries, with fantastic and friendly service!
Their cortado is da bomb diggity.
Great outdoor seating and fresh baked goods
Absolutely flavorless unsalted eggs and sausage biscuit / eggs bacon toast meal. The coffee was fine
Great coffee & staff
Great Coffee and food. Most recently had their vegetarian pie. Best coffee shop in this area for a few blocks.
Great food and service! The coffee is good too and the iced chai tea delicious!
One of my favorite local cafes! Great coffee and welcoming atmosphere
Service great, good vegan options- avocado toast excellent/ oat, soy and almond milk for coffee. Maybe a little pricey

It was a very brief visit, so can't say much. I only ordered my first ever avocado toast to go, advised by my friend. It was OK, but a bit too thin for full 7$. I mean, 5$ would totally be OK for that. Or maybe I got behind the times. Still nice place, prices like in Manhattan though, you get the idea.
Fantastic spot with great food and, most importantly, Abbotsford Road coffee.
Great baked treats and coffee. Excellent sandwiches too!
Good place to work, good coffee & great music selection!
Super yummy. Bacon and egg on brioche was delectable! Egg fluffy and flavorful and the delicate brioche was a great pairing.
Great coffee at reasonable prices. Great atmosphere. Staff were polite. I liked the decor. Peace full place. I went here with my colleague. This place was amazing. Services was amazing.
Great caffeinated beverages, better than Starbucks. The avocado toast was superb! Perfectly cooked egg and so flavorful. Looking forward to our next visit to try some more from the menu.
This is the best coffee that I've found in Brooklyn. Also nice to have in a proper cup which is harder to find than I thought it would be.
cute cafe
Hands down Best flavoured avacado toast in Brooklyn (so yummy) I'm coming back 😋❤
One of the rare places that serves chicken pie and great coffee
Cake bar...mmmmmm..
Best food
Great fresh healthy food!

Nice little place! Love the decor. Floating chairs looks very original. Other then that: - coffee indeed very worth the price - food (breakfast), good but I would question the price for the amount.  Overall very good experience, so deserves recommendation. I would stop by for a coffee and a treat rather then breakfast.

This petite coffee shop at the corner of 4th Ave and Carroll Street is bright and welcoming.  It proved a great and friendly place to get some work accomplished.  The latte was lovely and  avocado toast was outstanding!
This is a cute coffee shop! I had their ham and Swiss sandwich and ice coffee. The staff is top notch too. I accidentally spilled my coffee almost right away and they gave me a free refill.
Food is great, gf options available.
Love this place! Lots of seating, great coffee
Locals use it for coworking & the munchies r good.
Nice coffeeshop and cafe with a lot of seating and a lot of outlets! Food is pretty good too.  Also, an interesting quirk is a significant number of the employees are Australian.

It was a very brief visit, so can't say much. I only ordered my first ever avocado toast to go, advised by my friend. It was OK, but a bit too thin for full 7$. I mean, 5$ would totally be OK for that. Or maybe I got behind the times. Still nice place, prices like in Manhattan though, you get the idea.
Nice space, great coffee & bagel and good service.
Great smoke salmon
They have a small but tasty selection of cafe foods, and a handful of very unique drinks. My barista was incredibly bubbly and friendly and the vibe inside was very chill.

I work near Root Hill so I go in several times a day.  The staff is nice.  I usually order the avocado toast with my coffee; it’s a good belly fill.   The prices may be a bit steep (similar to Stsrbucks) but I use their frequent visitor card for a free drink after 10 purchases. Starbucks just opened up a block away but I still go here because the munchies selection is better. My only complaint is maybe having outlets on the freestanding tables against the wall but no biggie.
Awesome experience, great food and vibe, staff was friendly and helped narrow down our choices! Highly recommended!
Very busy, crowded and a little noisy.  However the vibe is good.  Also, my vegetable mince pie took a long time to be properly heated.  But the place was nice and the the folks polite.

We loved your coffee.   You make delicious soy Cappuccino.   Wish you would open a store in Boston area.   I, can't go back to Starbucks,  after having your coffee,  and you made a beautiful design on the top.   :)   please come to Boston.  Pamela Griffin
(Translated by Google) Very nice place, with good offers to eat.  (Original) Muy lindo lugar, con buenas ofertas para comer.
Good salty and sweet option for an amazing breakfast. Good coffee. Loved the avocado toast.

Great place to hangout and work for a while. Just watch out for the barrage of very young kids e their parents mid-afternoons when school gets out. Great espresso, very friendly staff, good food, free Wi-Fi.
Really nice place to stop for a coffee - especially a latte - shop has an industrial design
Best coffee for miles!
Brooklyn hipster's paradise
Just stopped by for wifi and coffee. Seemed nice, cute, clean. Vegetarian friendly food options. Good coffee (roasted by Natural Root.) Was a pleasant place to drop by and work for a few mins.

Warm and cozy spot with great tasting coffee! They also serve food- not gluten free- but very popular. The oatmeal and avocado toast with egg on top was popular amongst everyone. Free wifi and friendly staff make this a go-to spot for freelancers. It was a mix of workers and people meeting up for food so turnover was pretty fast.

(Translated by Google) A nice place, very nice to have a coffee with excellent pastry typical of the area. The staff is very helpful It has a bathroom for customers that is clean and tidy  (Original) Un bonito lugar, muy agradable para tomar un café con excelente pastelería típica de la zona. El personal es muy servicial Cuenta con baño para clientes que se encuentra limpio y ordenado
Great neighborhood coffee shop/cafe with surprisingly good food. Both the oatmeal (made with milk but they'll sub water or non-dairy milk) and omelette were tasty.
Great ambiance, coffee and food. I love the Tagore's cup!
Their drinks, especially their tumeric drink, Tagore's Cup, was deliciously layered. The aesthetic is fairly minimal and the atmosphere is low-key and easy. I will be back here again. And, soon.
Great cappucino, there is a bit room for strollers in there.  Has an outdoor bench area.
Love The cheese bureka
Solid hot chocolate, minimalist aesthetic, nice little place.
Very nice staff. Free wi-fi. Cold brew is hot coffee that's been made cold, not actual cold brew.
Great breakfast choices
Fresh baked goods and beverages are delicious, in a relaxed atmosphere. L
Nice food,  music and  staff.
Best latte I've ever had!
delicious pot pies and baked goods (especially the pot pies). good coffee and a good atmosphere
Quality across the board. Cappuccino, bacon, egg and cheese sandy, wifi
I got a chicken avocado sandwich and it was great!! Only downside is this place is slightly pricey.
SERIOUSLY good baked goods. Breakfast til late afternoon. Nice people, gorgeous space.
No kombucha as it was advertised and also phone number is out of service

Took a wrong turn on the subway and happily ended up here. Warner Brothers on the TV, swing/old rhythm & blues music playing made the atmosphere great, the dirty chai I ordered was perfect, the quinoa apple and cranberry cake was most and delicious. I wasn't sure exactly what I wanted, but the barista was very knowledgeable and helped me. A stupid mistake turned into a great coffee stop.

I fell in love with their coffee. After repeatedly stopping in for coffee I tried their food. Legit, their veggie burger is top 2 in my life. The baguette is also very fresh and great in their sandwiches.
I met my wife here for our first date. This place helped me start a family. Quiet ambiance led to a bar across the street and eventually babies!

Great coffee. I ordered coffee black with a ginger cookie. I really stopped by because I heard the coffee is always fresh and bold. It was. I would like to go back and try some other of their selections. I thought the waitress was okay. Service was good. Prices varied. Some were better than others. I would go back.
Excellent Americano.
Great place. The homemade blueberry muffin made is slamming!!!!
Sandwiches are always fresh and very good. They have great multigrain bread.
Solid cappuccino with an even more extensive baked goods selection. Their blueberry muffin is excellent. I need to come back for lunch and give their enticing salads a try.

This is, by far, my favorite coffee shop in the area.  While on the overpriced side, their sandwiches and salads are wonderful, and the pastries aren't too bad, either.  It's a small space, but when you can score a seat (late weekday afternoons are your best bet), it makes for a great study spot.  The wifi is free and relatively fast, and the decor is friendly and cozy.  The staff are all really, really, nice, and don't seem to mind if you stay there for awhile.  The coffee is *okay* - tasty though nothing to write home about.  I keep coming back for the friendly vibes and the fact that they don't kick me out for doing work here, as long as I keep caffeinating.
The best place in the slope to sit, work and drink coffee in the slope. It’s also a great bar and definitely try any variation of the Stuffed Jacket Potato.
Make yourself at home in this cafe. Great coffee, solid food, awesome wifi, and good Blue Sky muffins if they haven't ran out. The owner is usually running the counter, very friendly lady.
